CCB Project Management

Theo Killian

2021-04-21

Introduction

This document serves as a report on all of the requests received and projects currently completed by the CCB bioinformatics platform since 18 August 2020.

Projects

The CCB bioinformatics platform receives requests for bioinformatic assistance on various projects. The sections below explore the types and nature of these requested projects.

path <- "~/Documents/tmp/ccb_project_management/documents/"
ccb_proj_mgt <- read_excel(paste0(path, "/ccb_proj_mgt.xlsx"))
ccb_proj_mgt %>%
  dplyr::select(-c(remarks)) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(date_request = as.Date(date_request)) %>%
  dplyr::arrange(desc(date_request)) %>%
  DT::datatable()

Project Statistics

Statistics and figures on the CCB projects are generated in this report to better understand projects types and number of requests per lab at CCB-VIB.

Histogram of Project Types

Below is a histogram of the types of projects that have been requested by members of labs at CCB.

ccb_proj_mgt %>%
  group_by(project_type) %>%
  tally() %>%
  arrange(n) %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(
    project_type = factor(project_type, levels = unique(project_type))) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = project_type, y = n, fill = project_type)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  theme_classic() +
  xlab("Type of Projects") +
  ylab("Number of Projects") +
  scale_fill_viridis_d() +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  coord_flip() +
  ggtitle("Types of projects that have been requested by CCB labs") -> a1
a1

Below is a histogram of the subtypes of projects that have been requested by members of labs at CCB.

ccb_proj_mgt %>%

Histogram of Total Time Devoted to Projects

Below is a histogram that displays the rough time in hours devoted to each project that has been requested by labs at CCB. Note CCB donates generate infrastructure projects such as bulk RNAseq pipelines which will be used by many labs. Red dotted line represents the theoretical maximum time available to devote equally to each lab (i.e.40 hours a week, multiplied by 48 weeks, divided by 12 labs = approximately 180 hours available to service each lab per year. This calculation includes time spent in meetings, etc. but does not include time spent for general communally available infrastructure projects such as omics pipelines.)

ccb_temp1 <- ccb_proj_mgt
ccb_temp1 %>%
  dplyr::filter(lab == "Bergers/Lambrechts") -> pan_mouse
ccb_temp1 %>%
  dplyr::filter(!lab == "Bergers/Lambrechts") -> ccb_temp1
pan_hrs <- (pan_mouse$duration_hrs[1] / 2)
pan_mouse_1 <- pan_mouse
pan_mouse_2 <- pan_mouse
pan_mouse_1$lab[1] <- "Bergers"
pan_mouse_2$lab[1] <- "Lambrechts"
pan_mouse_1$duration_hrs <- pan_hrs
pan_mouse_2$duration_hrs <- pan_hrs
dplyr::bind_rows(pan_mouse_1, pan_mouse_2, ccb_temp1) -> ccb_temp2
ccb_temp2 %>%
  dplyr::group_by(lab) %>%
  summarise(total_hrs = sum(duration_hrs)) %>%
  arrange(total_hrs) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(lab = factor(lab, levels = unique(lab))) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = lab, y = total_hrs, fill = lab)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  theme_classic() +
  xlab("CCB labs") +
  ylab("Total lab hours") +
  scale_fill_viridis_d() +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 180, linetype = "dotted", color = "red") +
  coord_flip() +
  ggtitle("Total Time Devoted to CCB Projects by Lab") -> a3 
a3

Project Timeline

Below is a histogram that displays the number of projects requested per month for the period between August 2020 and February 2021.

ccb_proj_mgt %>%
  dplyr::mutate(months = months(as.POSIXlt(date_request, format = "%Y%m%d"))) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(months = factor(months, levels = unique(months))) %>%
  group_by(months) -> ccb_month
ccb_month %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = months, fill = months)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "count") +
    theme_classic() +
    ylim(0, 10) +
    ylab("Number of projects requested per month") +
    scale_fill_viridis_d() +
    theme(legend.position = "none") +
    ggtitle("Number of Projects requested per month since Aug 2020") -> a4
a4
